First Lady Michelle Obama will be traveling to China from March 19-26, 2014. She will visit Beijing, Xi'an, and Chengdu during her trip. In Beijing, she will meet with Madame Peng, the spouse of China's President Xi Jinping, and visit a university and high school. In Chengdu, she will also visit a high school. The First Lady will be accompanied by her mother and daughters. The focus of her trip is on the power and importance of education, and she will be visiting historical and cultural sites in China. Students in the US are encouraged to follow her trip and resources will be provided for classrooms to explore Chinese culture. Before her trip, she will visit the Washington Yu Ying Public Charter School in DC, where she will deliver remarks and interact with students. The school takes its name from a groundbreaking girls school founded in Beijing in 1911.